The paper discusses the generalization of neural networks, which is a topic commonly studied in the machine learning community. The concept of incremental learning dynamics is also a key focus, which falls under the category of optimization algorithms and their impact on learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also includes experiments with deep matrix sensing and linear networks for binary classification, which are relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and information theory (cs.IT), respectively.
